+frameInbox('Playtesting')
	div
		ul
			li.fragment an opportunity to find out the truth about your game
			li.fragment is conducted in a similar manner like usability testing in software
			li.fragment if it's too player-centric, the designer is in jeopardy of changing the concept to satisfy their audience
			li.fragment <span class="highlight">Playtest types</span>
				ul
					li.fragment internal - conducted by the team
					li.fragment design - conducted by people who understand game design
					li.fragment friend playtest - playtest by friends and relatives
					li.fragment target audience playtest
					li.fragment experienced player playtest - tested by experienced<br> players
			li.fragment it's important to track a many inputs as possible, including<br> the nonverbal ones
		.bottom-20.right-20
			img.height-400(src=imgAssets+'playtesting.png')
